JOHANNESBURG - Kaizer Chiefs have decided to take the Nedbank Cup Last 16 fixture against Stellenbosch FC, on 10 March,  to Durban’s Moses Mabhida Stadium. The PSL announced initially that the match would be played at the FNB Stadium in Gauteng. PREVIEW: The Soweto Derby and all that comes with it Amakhosi beat Golden Arrows 3-0 in the previous round, while Stellenbosch FC surprised first division log leaders Highlands Park, winning 1-0. Chiefs faced Stellenbosch in the Nedbank Cup Last 32 last season, winning convincingly, 3-0. The match was played at Athlone Stadium. African News Agency